## ğŸš€ Quick Start

### Prerequisites
- Node.js (v18 or higher)
- MongoDB Atlas or local instance
- Groq API account

### Installation

1. **Clone the repositories**
```bash
# Frontend
git clone https://github.com/josseycodes1/Funlearn-Frontend.git
cd Funlearn-Frontend

# Backend
git clone https://github.com/Kingsley-codes/funlearn-backend.git
cd funlearn-backend
```

2. **Install dependencies**
```bash
# Both frontend and backend
npm install
```

3. **Environment Configuration**

Create `.env` files in both projects:

**Backend (.env)**
```env
PORT=5000
MONGO_URI=your_mongodb_connection_string
JWT_SECRET=your_jwt_secret
JWT_EXPIRES_IN=7d
GROQ_URL=https://api.groq.com/openai/v1/chat/completions
GROQ_API_KEY=your_groq_api_key
CLOUDINARY_CLOUD_NAME=your_cloudinary_name
CLOUDINARY_API_KEY=your_cloudinary_api_key
CLOUDINARY_API_SECRET=your_cloudinary_api_secret
FRONTEND_URL=https://funlearn-frontend.vercel.app
VAPID_PUBLIC_KEY=your_vapid_public_key
VAPID_PRIVATE_KEY=your_vapid_private_key
VAPID_EMAIL=mailto:your_email
PINECONE_API_KEY=your_pinecone_api_key
PINECONE_INDEX_NAME=ai-chat-vectors
```

**Frontend (.env.local)**
```env
NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL=https://funlearn-backend-f3cg.onrender.com
```

4. **Run the applications**
```bash
# Backend
npm run server

# Frontend
npm run dev
```

